        <h1>Choose Outbound Caller ID &amp; P-Asserted-Identity</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="blog-article-content">

        <p>
          With GonoPBX v1.6.0, extensions that have multiple assigned numbers get much more control
          over outbound calls. Previously, the <strong>first assigned DID</strong> was always used as caller ID –
          now each extension can choose its own outbound number.
        </p>

        <h2>Choose outbound caller ID</h2>

        <p>
          A common scenario: a company has a number block (e.g., +4922166980 to +4922166989),
          and each employee has their own extension. Inbound calls work perfectly –
          but outbound calls used to show the same number every time.
        </p>

        <p>
          Starting with v1.6.0, the extension detail page shows a <strong>dropdown</strong> with all
          assigned numbers. Select the desired number, save – done.
          The selected DID will be used for all outbound calls as caller ID.
        </p>

        <p>
          If no selection is made, the previous behavior remains:
          the first assigned number is used as the default. Existing installations
          remain fully backward compatible.
        </p>

        <h2>P-Asserted-Identity (PAI) header</h2>

        <p>
          Many SIP providers require not only the caller ID but also a
          <strong>P-Asserted-Identity header</strong> (PAI) to verify the caller identity.
          This is especially important for number blocks where the head number
          must be sent as PAI.
        </p>

        <p>
          The extension detail page now includes an additional field for the PAI number.
          Enter the head number, e.g. <code>+4922166980</code>. GonoPBX will automatically
          generate the SIP header:
        </p>

        <pre><code>P-Asserted-Identity: &lt;sip:+4922166980@sip-server.provider.de&gt;</code></pre>

        <p>
          The domain is taken automatically from the assigned SIP trunk –
          no manual configuration needed.
        </p>

        <h2>Automatic safeguards</h2>

        <p>
          To prevent invalid configurations, GonoPBX checks:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>The selected caller ID <strong>must</strong> be one of the DIDs assigned to the extension</li>
          <li>If a number set as outbound CID is deleted, it is automatically reset to default</li>
          <li>The PAI field is optional – if left empty, no PAI header is sent</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to update</h2>

        <h3>Automatic (recommended)</h3>
        <p>
          In the GonoPBX web interface under <strong>Settings → Server → Update</strong>
          click “Install update”. The system pulls the latest version,
          rebuilds the containers, and restarts automatically.
        </p>

        <h3>Manual</h3>
        <pre><code>cd /root/asterisk-pbx-gui
git pull origin main
docker compose up -d --build</code></pre>

        <div class="blog-info-box">
          <p>
            <strong>Note:</strong> The database migration (new columns <code>outbound_cid</code>
            and <code>pai</code>) runs automatically when the backend starts –
            no manual steps required.
          </p>
        </div>

